Chamaerops humilis

   [4469.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Liliopsida:Arecidae:Arecales:Palmae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4469

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An evergreen tree (palm) with fan shaped leaves,
   producing only one stem and reaching up to 3 m in height but often
   smaller. The root may reach as deep as 5 m. USES Fibre is extracted
   from the leaves and mainly used for upholstery and ropes. It can be
   used for erosion control on slopes. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. COMMON
   NAMES Dwarf fan palm, European fan palm, Palmier nain, Crin vegetal,
   Doum, Tinerir, Vegetable horsetail, Algerian fibre, Indiafaser,
   Palmetto. FURTHER INF Dwarf fan palm is native of the Mediterraen
   region where it is found growing wild also in Italy, Spain, and France.
   It thrives best in soils with a clay horizont near the soil surface.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. humilis L.)
   White F 1983 pp 332 [RAIN, FER, DRA, DEP, TEXT, PH]
   Kirby R 1963 pp 372-379 [TEMP, TEXT, RAIN, USE]
   Rhem S 1991 pp 360 [USE]

